subject: Tennis
Wimbledon Tennis Tournament
lead_paragraph: Lindsay Davenport returned yesterday after taking almost a year off to have a child, losing a doubles match at the Pilot Pen in New Haven. Davenport and Lisa Raymond were beaten by Cara Black and Liezel Huber, 6-7 (1), 6-3 and 10-4 in the match tie breaker. Black and Huber have won six doubles titles this year, including the Australian Open and Wimbledon. “Obviously, this is the first step in a long process,” Davenport said.
